title: Telegram /skills response renders raw HTML tags instead of rich formatted message
---
Running /skills from Telegram returns a plain-text message littered with <code> tags and raw HTML instead of a properly rendered rich-formatted message (monospace blocks, bold headings, collapsible sections, etc.).

Expected: /skills output should render like /tools — using Telegram-supported Markdown/HTML formatting so it displays natively as a rich message.

Observed: Raw tags visible in the message body, suggesting the skill-list output is being sent as plain text rather than through the Telegram HTML/Markdown formatter.